Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
saveOaBlackboxes(25.10)                                saveOaBlackboxes(25.10)

Name
       saveOaBlackboxes  -  Saves  the specified blackbox abstracts, using the
       OpenAccess database format

Syntax
       saveOaBlackboxes

       [-help]

       -cell <list_of_cells>

       -lib <libName>

       [-view <viewName>]

       Saves the specified blackbox abstracts, using the  OpenAccess  database
       format.  You can use the saveOaBlackboxes command at any time after im-
       porting the design.

       Note that when the design is saved using the  saveDesign  command,  the
       tool  automatically  saves  abstracts for any blackboxes in the design.
       However, if you are performing pin  optimization  or  manipulating  the
       blockages on a particular macro in the design, you may wish to save the
       abstract  for  only that particular macro. The saveOaBlackboxes command
       is useful in such situations.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each saveOaBlackboxes parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man  saveOaBlackboxes

       -cell <list_of_cells>
              Specifies one or more blackboxes to save. If  you  specify  more
              than one blackbox, you must enclose them in either double quota-
              tion  marks  or  curly  braces,  and separate them with an empty
              space.

       -lib <libName>
              Specifies the OpenAccess library to use to save the blackbox ab-
              stracts. If an OpenAccess library with the same name already ex-
              ists, the software creates a cell view in that library.

              If the library does not exist, the software creates the  library
              in  the  working  directory,  with the library name and the path
              name being the same. If a new library is created, the technology
              file is copied from the technology library to the new library.

       -view <viewName>
              Specifies the cell view to save.

              Default: Uses the view name abstract

Examples
              * The following command saves the  blackbox  myBlackbox  in  the
                view abstract:

                saveOaBlackboxes -lib myLib -cell myBlackbox -view abstract

              * The following command saves the blackboxes myBlackbox1 and my-
                Blackbox2 in the view abstract:

                saveOaBlackboxes  -lib  myLib  -cell "myBlackbox1 myBlackbox2"
                -view abstract

              * The following command also saves  the  blackboxes  myBlackbox1
                and myBlackbox2 in the view abstract:

                saveOaBlackboxes  -lib  myLib  -cell {myBlackbox1 myBlackbox2}
                -view abstract

